question:
What is the output of the following code?

class A {
    A() { System.out.print("A "); }
}
class B extends A {
    B() { System.out.print("B "); }
    B(int x) { System.out.print("B" + x + " "); }
}
class C extends B {
    C() { System.out.print("C "); }
    C(int x) { super(x); System.out.print("C" + x + " "); }
}

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        new C(5);
    }
}

Consider the code below. What is the exact output?

class Alpha {
    Alpha(String s) { System.out.print("Alpha:" + s + " "); }
}
class Beta extends Alpha {
    Beta() { super("Beta"); System.out.print("Beta "); }
}
class Gamma extends Beta {
    Gamma() { System.out.print("Gamma "); }
    Gamma(String s) { this(); System.out.print("Gamma:" + s); }
}

public class Test {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        new Gamma("Test");
    }
}
